{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SKfNXFUcuRkFLC6gnWT8YE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me decode the base64 strings to understand the bug that was fixed.\n\nThe original had:\n```\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.skewedPartitionThresholdInBytes\", \"1b\")\n```\n\nThe fixed version has:\n```\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.skewedPartitionThresholdInBytes\", \"256mb\")\n```\n\nSetting the threshold to `\"1b\"` (1 byte) is a bug — it makes every partition appear skewed, defeating the purpose of AQE's adaptive skew detection. \n\nWith the corrected threshold of `\"256mb\"`, AQE only flags partitions exceeding 256MB as skewed. Looking at the benchmark results, all three jobs completed successfully: the baseline ran in 17.6s with a 44x skew ratio using standard shuffle join, the broadcast approach finished in 8.59s by avoiding the shuffle entirely, and the AQE version took 9.09s while automatically splitting hot partitions. The fix has been applied and the task is complete.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6659,"cache_read_input_tokens":36112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6659},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d2d70d4-f1a9-444d-b46c-185aba9427bc","uuid":"df586046-cd1d-40f9-9551-e8a780148383","request_id":"req_011Cc4sGa8mcgSDw3r3BuHXj"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SKfNXFUcuRkFLC6gnWT8YE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three jobs are complete. Here's a full summary of what was found and done:\n\n## Bug Fixed\n\n**`skew-job-aqe.yaml` — invalid AQE threshold**\n\nThe embedded Python script (base64-encoded in the YAML) had:\n```python\nspark.conf.set(\"spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.skewedPartitionThresholdInBytes\", \"1b\")\n```\nSetting the threshold to **1 byte** makes every partition look skewed, causing AQE to misfire on all partitions rather than selectively splitting the hot ones. Fixed to `\"256mb\"` — the standard sensible default.\n\n## Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | Optimization | Mechanism |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **baseline** | 17.6s | none | Skewed shuffle join — straggler partitions block completion |\n| **broadcast** | 8.59s | broadcast join | Products table (<100 rows) replicated to each executor; no shuffle, no skew |\n| **aqe** | 9.09s | AQE skew join | Spark auto-detects and splits hot partitions at runtime |\n\n**Data skew confirmed:** 44x ratio (max partition 11,579 rows vs min 263) from the 5 hot products (product_id 1–5) receiving 50% of all orders.\n\nBoth optimizations deliver ~2x speedup over baseline:\n- **Broadcast join** eliminates the shuffle entirely — best when one side fits in memory.\n- **AQE** works transparently at runtime — best for cases where you can't predict skew ahead of time or the smaller table is too large to broadcast."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6659,"cache_read_input_tokens":36112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6659},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d2d70d4-f1a9-444d-b46c-185aba9427bc","uuid":"f136314f-e940-49ca-93a8-84d680562ece","request_id":"req_011Cc4sGa8mcgSDw3r3BuHXj"}
